But having been subdued by most grievous Slaughters, they have at length laid down their Fierceness, and are forced to bear the Yoke. The Christians‚ partly through Fear of the Rage of the Jews, and partly through an intemperate Zeal for Christianity‚ have endeavoured either whol- ly to destroy by various Miseries this dispersed People, or to tire them out by the Grievousness and Length of their Miseries, and thus to compel them to profess the Christian Faith. Upon this account various Ediets have at different Times proceeded against the Jews.
